WorkoutDescription: Duration: 70 minutes Course: Flat or rolling hills Purpose: Increase aerobic capacity, learn to embrace the feeling of imminent death Workout: Super-Fun Intervals (or ‚ÄúFuntervals‚Äù as I like to call them); 2 sets of 3 x 3-minute intervals Do 3 3-minute intervals with 3 minutes of easy spinning between; spend the first 30-45 seconds of each interval gradually increasing power to the maximum you think you can hold for the duration of the interval (watts: 260+++), then hold it there until the 3 minutes are up After the first set of 3 intervals, recover for 8 minutes (watts: 115 and below), then do your second set of 3 3-minute intervals with 3 minutes of rest between each; ride recovery pace for at least 10 minutes after the last interval

Title: Super "Funtervals"
WorkoutDescription: Super-Funtervals!!!!!! (***see below) Duration: 75 minutes 3x2 minutes, 2 minutes recovery between intervals (3 sets) 8 minutes recovery between sets ***Super-Funtervals are best done without using Workout mode, otherwise you‚Äôll likely end up in the cadence death-spiral. Unlike regular Funtervals, which are more of a steady effort, Super-Funtervals start with a hard acceleration. Attempt to hit and hold high wattage (above 300), but expect to start fading about halfway through the interval; keep the cadence above 90rpm throughout, and try to fight through the lactic build-up and surge again at the very end of the 2-minute period. The 2-minute recovery between intervals should feel too short for full recovery.

Title: Cycling
AthleteComments: *10/14/2019 Abigail Snyder: I suppose how I feel depends on when you ask. I felt GREAT for the first 30 miles. Then I went from fatigued to out of water to hard bonk by mile 35. I should have taken a bottle at the middle aid station... lesson learned. I got a bottle at the last aid station (mile 40), but by then I was toast. That first half was beautiful. I rode well, both power and technically. I got stopped up a bit getting into the singletrack, so I know next time I need to really push to get in there before some of the roadies who have a lot of power but not great handling. Eventually it thinned out and I rocked it. Lost time early on an aggressive pass that didn‚Äôt work out, but came back and ended up passing those girls anyway. No flats. Seriously huge. Thanks Jesus... I was literally praying most of the race for good lines and no flats. After I bonked, my power just tanked. I had to unclip a few times because I just couldn‚Äôt power through a few sections and looked down at one point on the greenway and I was working to do just 140 watts. Ugh. With better hydration and nutrition, I think I could nail it. Next time.*
